<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.95/5452: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-30T13:00:00+08:00">July 30, 1932—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 30—7:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>875. Following from American Consul at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“July 29, 6 p.m. Spokesman of Japanese military headquarters
                                    confirms press report that Japanese detachment defeated 3,000
                                    volunteers near Suichung after heavy fighting with considerable
                                    casualties.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>